Charles Duff (21 April 1794 – 1848) was an English professional cricketer who played first-class cricket from 1824 to 1830.
He played for Sussex and made 12 known appearances in first-class matches.

response: Charles Duff (7 April 1894 – 15 October 1966) was a Northern Irish author of books on language learning. He also wrote a popular book on hanging and other means of execution.Introduction to A Handbook on Hanging Retrieved 1 March 2016.
